main event: Two witnesses reported seeing an unidentified object in Kettering, Ohio, on May 27, 1966.
interesting points: The sighting lasted between 3 to 5 minutes,The object was moving in a SSW direction,The conclusion was that the object was a probable satellite, ECHO II,One witness's mother also confirmed seeing the object,The weather conditions were bright with no physical evidence.
witness description: A 23-year-old female witness and her mother.
